        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 9:22PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 922 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles east of Cope, or 19 miles west of Bonny Reservoir, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail. Accumulating
hail may be possible with this storm.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central Yuma
County, including the following locations... Kirk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
